quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  17,87,excepting by some mercy of thy Lord; surly His favour to thee is great
  17,88,"Say: 'If men and jinn banded together to produce the like of this Koran, they would never produce its like, not though they backed one another"
  17,89,We have indeed turned about for men in this Koran every manner of similitude; yet most men refuse all but unbelief
  17,90,"They say, 'We will not believe thee till thou makest a spring to gush forth from the earth for us"
  17,91,"or till thou possessest a garden of plants and vines, and thou makest rivers to gush forth abundantly all amongst it"
  17,92,"or till thou makest heaven to fall, as thou assertest, on us in fragments, or thou bringest God and the angels as a surety"
  17,93,"or till thou possessest a house of gold ornament, or till thou goest up into heaven; and we will not believe thy going up till thou bringest down on us a book that we may read. Say: 'Glory be to my Lord. Am I aught but a mortal, a Messenger"
  17,94,"And naught prevented men from believing when the guidance came to them, but that they said, 'Has God sent forth a mortal as Messenger"
  17,95,"Say: 'Had there been in the earth angels walking. at peace, We would have sent down upon them out of heaven an angel as Messenger"
  17,96,"Say: 'God suffices as a witness between me and you; surely He is aware of and sees His servants"